1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
 Well, Merry Christmas to you all.

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:04,500
 (Audience) Merry Christmas.

3
00:00:04,500 --> 00:00:06,000
 Sing dann, Pfeilock.

4
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:07,300
 (Laughter)

5
00:00:07,300 --> 00:00:11,160
 And as I created my own song, but it's not my original,

6
00:00:11,160 --> 00:00:15,300
 I want to wish you a sing dann, Pfeilock.

7
00:00:15,300 --> 00:00:17,700
 I want to wish you ...

8
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:19,360
 (Singing) ... a Pfeilock.

9
00:00:19,360 --> 00:00:22,660
 I want to wish you a sing dann, Pfeilock,

10
00:00:22,660 --> 00:00:26,000
 from the bottom of my heart.

11
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:28,000
 (Applause)

12
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:30,000
 (Cheers)

13
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,000
 Yeah, that was not fully planned in that way,

14
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:35,000
 but good to see you all.

15
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:38,000
 Hey, I don't know about you,

16
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:42,000
 but some things that I appreciate about Christmas in Hong Kong

17
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:47,000
 are all these beautiful, incredible decorations.

18
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:51,000
 We have them in the malls, where they put up these awesome displays,

19
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:54,000
 you know, outside on the buildings, in some public areas,

20
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:57,000
 and it really is spectacular.

21
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:01,000
 Hong Kong really knows how to dazzle, right?

22
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:03,000
 Another thing I appreciate is,

23
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:06,000
 you can be walking through the mall during Christmas,

24
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:10,000
 and you can hear an actual Christmas carol in the mall,

25
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:11,000
 which is also amazing.

26
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:13,000
 That doesn't happen in every country.

27
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:14,000
 That's incredible.

28
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:18,000
 And then I also appreciate, maybe more out of selfish reasons,

29
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:23,000
 I appreciate also all the imported Christmas goodies and treats.

30
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:25,000
 Because they also import things from Germany,

31
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:28,000
 so I always buy some Christmas treats from Germany.

32
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:32,000
 We had some earlier, I think they're all gone now, sorry.

33
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,000
 But I really enjoy that.

34
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:38,000
 But if we're honest, you know, there's all of this buzz,

35
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:40,000
 and it raises a question,

36
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:48,000
 why remember and celebrate Jesus' birth 2,000 years later?

37
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:50,000
 Why do we do that?

38
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:55,000
 That's what I want to explore today on this Christmas day.

39
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:58,000
 Now, in the Gospel of John,

40
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:03,000
 which is one of four of the books in the Bible that tell the story of Jesus,

41
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:06,000
 it's a little bit different than Matthew and Luke,

42
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:09,000
 who have a birth story from Jesus.

43
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:12,000
 But he has a theological statement,

44
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:16,000
 where he tells us about Jesus coming to this world,

45
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:18,000
 and the word becoming flesh.

46
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:22,000
 So I want to read from you from John 1, verse 14, it says this,

47
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:27,000
 "The word became flesh and made his dwelling among us.

48
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:32,000
 We have seen his glory, the glory of the one and only Son,

49
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:36,000
 who came from the Father full of grace and truth."

50
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:43,000
 Now, in the Gospel of John, there are several "I am" statements.

51
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:45,000
 So there's actually seven.

52
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:48,000
 And we've been looking, as we've been journeying towards Christmas,

53
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:51,000
 we've been looking at, "I am the light of the world."

54
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,000
 "I am the good shepherd."

55
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:56,000
 "I am the bread and the life."

56
00:02:56,000 --> 00:03:00,000
 And then, "I am the true vine."

57
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:03,000
 And today we're going to look at a fifth one.

58
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:05,000
 And these statements are very significant

59
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:10,000
 because it's Jesus actually explaining himself.

60
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:14,000
 He's talking about himself and the purpose and the meaning of himself.

61
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:18,000
 And so we should pay special attention to that.

62
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:22,000
 And we're going to look at one statement that helps us understand more

63
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:26,000
 the meaning of Christmas and why we do celebrate Christmas

64
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:31,000
 and why this is a joyous occasion that we celebrate.

65
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:35,000
 So let me set the context for these words from Jesus.

66
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:37,000
 So Jesus, he is with his disciples.

67
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:40,000
 It's actually a farewell moment.

68
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,000
 And he tells them some quite disturbing news.

69
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:46,000
 He tells them that one of them will betray them.

70
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:50,000
 He tells them that Peter, who was the leader amongst the disciples,

71
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:54,000
 that he's going to deny Jesus three times.

72
00:03:54,000 --> 00:04:00,000
 And he tells them that he's going to go to a place

73
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:02,000
 where the disciples cannot follow, to his father's house.

74
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,000
 He's going to prepare a place for them.

75
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:07,000
 And then he's going to come back and get them.

76
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:11,000
 And so the disciples, they're confused by all this news

77
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:13,000
 that it's hard to process.

78
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:15,000
 They're actually fearful.

79
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:21,000
 And all of this prompts a question, a question that Thomas asked.

80
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:24,000
 And so I want to pick up where Thomas asked this question.

81
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:27,000
 It's John 14, verse 5 and 6.

82
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:34,000
 And it says this, "Thomas said to him, 'Lord, we do not know where you are going.

83
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:37,000
 How can we know the way?'

84
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:41,000
 And Jesus said, 'I am the way, the truth, and the life.

85
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:46,000
 No one comes to the Father except through me.'"

86
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:48,000
 So Thomas is confused.

87
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:51,000
 He's thinking of a literal place, and he wants to know the way.

88
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:53,000
 He wants to understand, "Jesus, how can I be with you?

89
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:57,000
 How can I get to that place?"

90
00:04:57,000 --> 00:05:01,000
 And we also have these types of questions that Thomas is holding.

91
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:03,000
 We also ask about the way.

92
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:06,000
 We might not ask them to God, but we have questions about the way.

93
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:09,000
 We ask, "What's the way to success?

94
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:11,000
 What's the way to a meaningful life?

95
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:19,000
 What's the way to feeling whole because we're broken and things are difficult?

96
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:23,000
 How can I feel normal or well again?"

97
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:27,000
 And so we also pose these questions.

98
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:30,000
 And we're looking for this direction.

99
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:33,000
 Now, as I was preparing for this message,

100
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:37,000
 I had to think of a time when I literally was looking for directions.

101
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:40,000
 So a friend of mine and I, we were hiking--

102
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:42,000
 or actually, let me start over here.

103
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:47,000
 We were in Hawaii on a vacation in Maui, the island of Maui.

104
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:50,000
 And there was a big volcano, the Haleakala.

105
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:54,000
 And it's 3,055 meters high.

106
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:57,000
 And we read that there's a beautiful sunset,

107
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:59,000
 so we drove up to the top of the mountain,

108
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:02,000
 and we enjoyed the spectacular sunset.

109
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:06,000
 And then afterwards, we decided we are going to descend into the volcano,

110
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:10,000
 and 800-meter descent, altitude difference,

111
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:12,000
 and we're going to enjoy the landscape,

112
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:18,000
 even though our travel guide warned us not to go without a travel guide.

113
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:24,000
 And the reason why not to do that was because there's not much water in there.

114
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:26,000
 There's altitude sickness because it's very high,

115
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:29,000
 and you can suddenly feel good and have problems.

116
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:35,000
 But then also because of weather changes--it's hot, it's cold, it's foggy.

117
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,000
 There's all of that.

118
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:40,000
 But my friend and I were young, we're fearless, so we go in there.

119
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:42,000
 And it was amazing.

120
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:45,000
 It's a landscape like I've never seen before.

121
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:48,000
 It's like you're walking on the moon or something like that.

122
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,000
 It's absolutely incredible.

123
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:53,000
 And also quite--even a diverse type of landscape, even within there.

124
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:56,000
 And so we ran out of water.

125
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:59,000
 Thank God, a little bit afterwards, there was a hut,

126
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:01,000
 and there was one water source,

127
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:04,000
 and a person there encouraged us, "Better fill up all your bottles with water."

128
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:06,000
 So we got water again.

129
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:08,000
 So we keep hiking.

130
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:10,000
 We run out of water again.

131
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:12,000
 We finish all our food.

132
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,000
 We're totally lost.

133
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:16,000
 We have no idea where we're at.

134
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:18,000
 Every time we meet someone, which wasn't very often,

135
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:21,000
 we ask them for directions, and we cannot--

136
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:24,000
 they say, "You go here, and you turn right, and you'll never find here."

137
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:27,000
 So we're just completely a mess.

138
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:31,000
 And then it gets misty, and we can't see anything.

139
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:35,000
 And our clothes get wet, our pants get wet, our shoes get wet,

140
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:37,000
 and we're in trouble.

141
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:39,000
 And so finally we meet someone, and he says--

142
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,000
 we're like, "We want to get back to the summit."

143
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:44,000
 He's like, "Well, you hike a little bit this way, and there's a zigzag

144
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:46,000
 that goes up this steep wall.

145
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:48,000
 Take that, and that leads you to the summit."

146
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,000
 We're like, "Okay." So we find it actually, finally.

147
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:52,000
 So you go up the zigzag path.

148
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,000
 Now, to me, it felt like it was three hours.

149
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:57,000
 It probably was like an hour or an hour and a half.

150
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:59,000
 But it was super hard work.

151
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:02,000
 It was pretty much straight up.

152
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:06,000
 And so we get to the top, and my friend is so exhausted.

153
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:09,000
 I mean, he sits down. He cannot walk anymore.

154
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:11,000
 And then we see a parking lot, we see a street,

155
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:13,000
 but we're sitting there for an hour,

156
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:16,000
 and I'm pretty much in the same place as he is.

157
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:18,000
 I'm just done.

158
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:21,000
 So finally, after an hour, we manage to get ourselves up,

159
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:25,000
 and we walk towards the road, and there's a sign.

160
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:29,000
 And the sign says, "The summit is seven miles away."

161
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:32,000
 Eleven kilometers.

162
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,000
 And so our hearts sank.

163
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:38,000
 We're like, "There's no way in our condition that we can make this.

164
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:40,000
 There is no way."

165
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:44,000
 And so what we were, we were in need of rescue.

166
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:49,000
 We needed somebody to come and rescue us.

167
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:51,000
 And this is what Christmas is about,

168
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:57,000
 because Christmas is a rescue story.

169
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,000
 A lot of times you don't think about Christmas that way,

170
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:01,000
 but it is a rescue story,

171
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:05,000
 where we need somebody to come and get us and rescue us.

172
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:08,000
 Well, you might ask, "Rescue from what?"

173
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:12,000
 Well, let me set the context for that a little bit.

174
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:14,000
 In the first book of the Bible, in Genesis,

175
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:17,000
 God talks about creation and creating the world good,

176
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:20,000
 and he talks about four relational contexts.

177
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:24,000
 Us and God, us and ourselves,

178
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:28,000
 us and others, and us and creation.

179
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:31,000
 And he blessed it, and there's shalom, there's peace, there's wholeness,

180
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:33,000
 and all these relationships.

181
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,000
 You know, and that's amazing.

182
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:38,000
 But then, sin enters the world.

183
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:40,000
 Adam and Eve, they rebel against God,

184
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:42,000
 they do what they know is not right,

185
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:45,000
 and all these four relational contexts, they're ruptured.

186
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:47,000
 You know, we're separated from God,

187
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:51,000
 there's breakdown in our relationship to ourselves,

188
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:54,000
 there's shame, we're carrying shame and guilt,

189
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:57,000
 there is breakdown in relationship with each other,

190
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:59,000
 there's blaming,

191
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:02,000
 and there's also breakdown in relationship

192
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:05,000
 even to God's beautiful creation that we're meant to steward,

193
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:09,000
 which we now so often just destroy and exploit,

194
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:13,000
 instead of stewarding in the way that God asks us to.

195
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:16,000
 Now, in some sense, we might feel like,

196
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:19,000
 "Well, I don't, you know, like, sin ruptured all of this,

197
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:22,000
 this just happened to us, we have nothing to do with it."

198
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:25,000
 But the reality is we all contribute to it, every single one of us.

199
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:28,000
 Yes, we're impacted by what has happened, and by others,

200
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:32,000
 but we all contribute to this.

201
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:36,000
 We all do things out of selfishness that hurt others,

202
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:40,000
 we all say things we shouldn't say, or we regret that we said,

203
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:43,000
 and there's just this brokenness, it's just part of our lives.

204
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:47,000
 So this perfect world, these perfect relationships,

205
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:49,000
 that's not our experience.

206
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:52,000
 So this is a sobering reality.

207
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:55,000
 This is a sobering reality.

208
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:58,000
 And Christmas is sobering because there is a problem,

209
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:00,000
 there is an issue.

210
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:02,000
 This is part of that sobering reality,

211
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:05,000
 that we are in need of intervention,

212
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:08,000
 we are in need of rescue.

213
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:12,000
 Now, if you ever doubt if sin and evil are real,

214
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:14,000
 then ask yourself these questions.

215
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:18,000
 Why do you need to lock your door in your house?

216
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:22,000
 Why do you have to be protective of your children?

217
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:25,000
 Why are there hit and runs,

218
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:27,000
 where somebody hits somebody with a car,

219
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:31,000
 and then just drives on and let the person lay there to die?

220
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:35,000
 You know, why is there so much conflict in relationships?

221
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:37,000
 And we just can't keep help ourselves, and it just keeps happening,

222
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:39,000
 we keep doing things we don't want to do,

223
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:42,000
 and hurt each other, and it just sucks.

224
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:48,000
 Why are there wars, injustice, racism?

225
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:51,000
 So we have a sin problem,

226
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:56,000
 it runs through us, not past us, all of us.

227
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:59,000
 And we're in need of rescue.

228
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:05,000
 We need rescue, we cannot fix ourselves.

229
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:11,000
 And like Thomas, we ask, "How do we fix this mess? What do we do?"

230
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:13,000
 And people come up with solutions,

231
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:16,000
 "Well, we just got to teach and educate, and then everything will be fine."

232
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:21,000
 Well, we've been teaching and educating for forever, and it's not fine.

233
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:24,000
 Some think, "Oh, if this political party gets in charge,

234
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:27,000
 then everything will be solved, if you follow this political ideology,

235
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:31,000
 then everything will be okay, everything will be brought back in harmony."

236
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:34,000
 Well, we've had many different political parties,

237
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:36,000
 and it has never happened.

238
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:41,000
 We are in need of rescue, we cannot fix ourselves.

239
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:44,000
 And that's into these questions that we hold,

240
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:46,000
 "How do we fix this?"

241
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:49,000
 That Jesus speaks these words in verse 6, he says,

242
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:53,000
 "I am the way, the truth, and the life.

243
00:12:53,000 --> 00:13:00,000
 Nobody comes through the Father except through me."

244
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:04,000
 And I want to unpack the way, the truth, the life,

245
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:06,000
 I want to unpack that in a little bit different order,

246
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:08,000
 because Jesus says he is the truth.

247
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:10,000
 What does that mean?

248
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:13,000
 It means that Jesus is the revelation of God, is God in the flesh.

249
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:17,000
 He shows us who God is, but he also shows us who we are,

250
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:22,000
 the truth about ourselves, that there is brokenness in our lives,

251
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:25,000
 that there are issues.

252
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:28,000
 So Jesus is the truth.

253
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:32,000
 He shows us how things really are,

254
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:36,000
 and we can know the truth as we get to know him.

255
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:40,000
 Then secondly, Jesus is the life.

256
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:44,000
 Jesus was part of creation, creating this world.

257
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:46,000
 He is God.

258
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:48,000
 So he brought life into being.

259
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:52,000
 He is the source of life, and in him there is life.

260
00:13:52,000 --> 00:14:00,000
 And he has brought life to us and brings also eternal life into this world.

261
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:10,000
 And it's because he came here to die for our sins on behalf of us,

262
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:13,000
 because we were guilty.

263
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:16,000
 And there was a sentence that was demanded,

264
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:19,000
 and to remove the guilt from us and to give us life,

265
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:22,000
 to give us the gift of the Holy Spirit,

266
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:25,000
 to pour the Holy Spirit into our lives,

267
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:30,000
 so that the power of sin, the enslavement to sin,

268
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:35,000
 that the power of death, the power of evil is broken over our lives.

269
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:40,000
 And then when we do that, the Bible talks about that we are born again,

270
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:43,000
 that we cross over from death to life,

271
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:48,000
 because we are given a new life, we're set on a new trajectory.

272
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:52,000
 We do not now have to live in brokenness any longer.

273
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:55,000
 Change has begun.

274
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:59,000
 And God also says that one day he will complete his work,

275
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:02,000
 where all of our brokenness, all of our pains, all of our sorrows,

276
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:05,000
 all of our tears, all the difficult things that we're holding,

277
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:10,000
 that he will restore them and bring wholeness.

278
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:12,000
 And that is some good news, isn't that?

279
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:15,000
 Because we need it.

280
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:19,000
 But then Jesus also says, "I am the way."

281
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:21,000
 And the way is not good advice.

282
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:24,000
 Jesus didn't give Thomas some good advice right there.

283
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:26,000
 He's like, "Let me give you some advice."

284
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:29,000
 I love giving advice. Germans love giving advice.

285
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:33,000
 Let me tell you.

286
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:37,000
 It's not a system of beliefs.

287
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:43,000
 You need to believe this exact system, and then everything will be okay.

288
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:46,000
 No, the way is a person.

289
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:48,000
 It is a person of Jesus.

290
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:50,000
 And if we have a relationship with the way,

291
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:52,000
 if we have a relationship with Jesus,

292
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:56,000
 that's how we are brought out of our mess.

293
00:15:56,000 --> 00:16:00,000
 That's where healing is brought into our circumstances,

294
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:03,000
 into whatever it is that we're carrying, whatever it is that we're holding,

295
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:05,000
 whatever it is that we're going through,

296
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:10,000
 that he brings his peace, that he brings his grace,

297
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:14,000
 that he brings his mercy, that he brings his love,

298
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:17,000
 that he gives us his presence.

299
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:20,000
 Now what's interesting, I want to set a little bit more the context of these words,

300
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:22,000
 that I am the way, the truth, and the life,

301
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:25,000
 that nobody comes to the Father except through me.

302
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:32,000
 So Jesus says that the night before he goes to the cross to lay down his life.

303
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:39,000
 Now, if good advice or five principles or a belief system were good enough,

304
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:43,000
 Jesus would not need to go to the cross.

305
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:47,000
 Then he could have just told Thomas, "Hey Thomas, you know, just do this."

306
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:50,000
 But that's not what he does.

307
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:53,000
 He tells him that he is the way and that he is the only way,

308
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:57,000
 and that it's through him that we overcome these things.

309
00:16:57,000 --> 00:17:00,000
 And that is good news.

310
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:02,000
 That's the joyous news of Christmas.

311
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:05,000
 That's why we sing joy to the world.

312
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:11,000
 Because Jesus has come to bring us life and fullness,

313
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:14,000
 or life to the full, as the Gospel of John talks about.

314
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:17,000
 And to restore us back to the Father,

315
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:21,000
 and to bring wholeness into every facet of our relationships with ourselves,

316
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:25,000
 with others, with God, with creation.

317
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:31,000
 And one day he will set all that was broken by sin, he will set it right.

318
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:36,000
 So the good news of Christmas is that Jesus has come to restore us to the Father.

319
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:39,000
 Everyone is invited to receive him,

320
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:49,000
 and experience the forgiveness, joy, and healing that is found only in a relationship with him.

321
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:54,000
 So when Jesus declared that he is the way, I am the way, the truth, and the life,

322
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:56,000
 this is truly good news.

323
00:17:56,000 --> 00:18:02,000
 And this is why, even 2,000 years later, we celebrate Christmas.

324
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:06,000
 Yes, Christmas acknowledges that it's sobering.

325
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:09,000
 Because we need it, we're broken people, we need him to act,

326
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:13,000
 to move in our lives, in this world, in our neighborhoods, in the city.

327
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:16,000
 But it's also joyful, because God has acted,

328
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:23,000
 and one day he will act again to complete this work of healing and restoration that he has started.

329
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:29,000
 So earlier I started a story, actually didn't finish it, right?

330
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:35,000
 We're still standing at the sign, 7 miles up the mountain, 11 kilometers up, hearts sinking.

331
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:39,000
 How are you thinking about? I don't know.

332
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:42,000
 So we're sinking at the traffic sign,

333
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:48,000
 and honestly my friend and I, we don't know what to do.

334
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:53,000
 So he became a Christian like a year ago, I was a Christian for 6, 7 years.

335
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:57,000
 So we prayed with Jesus, send us a car that can take us back up to the hill.

336
00:18:57,000 --> 00:19:02,000
 10 minutes later, a car starts coming up the road, a pickup truck, we do the hitchhiking.

337
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:05,000
 Do you do that in Hong Kong this way here? No?

338
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:08,000
 Well, you do it this way in the US.

339
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:13,000
 And so the truck stops, we jump in the back of the pickup truck, he takes us all the way to the top.

340
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:21,000
 And when we get out, he told us, "Hey, you guys are so lucky, there's hardly any more cars coming here tonight."

341
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:26,000
 And besides him, our car was the only one in the parking lot.

342
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:32,000
 So Jesus sent us rescue when we needed it, and we really, really needed it.

343
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:35,000
 Now I want to invite the worship team to come up.

344
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:49,000
 Today, on this Christmas day, we celebrate a much greater work of rescue than my friend and I being rescued on the hill.

345
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:51,000
 And we didn't really need it.

346
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:55,000
 But we celebrate a much greater rescue.

347
00:19:55,000 --> 00:20:00,000
 Because we can't save ourselves, we can't rescue ourselves.

348
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:03,000
 It's outside of our power, it's outside of what we're able to do.

349
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:14,000
 And the Creator of the universe, He humbled Himself, was born as a child, entered our pain, our sorrow, our sinful world,

350
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:22,000
 and died on the cross for our sins, so that we can be forgiven, that we can have life, a new life in Him,

351
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:31,000
 that we can have hope, that we can have what we call salvation, that we can receive the gift of the Holy Spirit living within us,

352
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:35,000
 and that we can receive a new life in Him.

353
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:38,000
 And that is amazing news.

354
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:45,000
 We don't have to climb up to God, because God has come down to us.

355
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:52,000
 And He has come down to every single one of us, and to whatever it is that is going on, that you are walking through,

356
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:58,000
 that's weighing down your heart, your life, the tears that have been flowing at night or wherever you are.

357
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:08,000
 He has come down to you, because He wants to meet you, He wants to bring you to Himself,

358
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:13,000
 to give you a new hope and a new life in Him.

359
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:17,000
 Now how do you receive this new hope and this new life?

360
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:24,000
 Well, we do it through faith, through trust in Jesus.

361
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:27,000
 Now what does that mean?

362
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:34,000
 Well, we believe that Jesus is who He says He is, that He is the way, that He is the truth, that He is the life.

363
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:41,000
 And it doesn't have to mean that we perfectly understand everything, but we understand that He is the one that can help us.

364
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:45,000
 And then we come to Him and we pray, because that's an act of faith.

365
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:57,000
 And so what I want to do is I want to invite you to pray this prayer along with me if you want to receive this gift that Jesus offers.

366
00:21:57,000 --> 00:22:00,000
 Yeah?

367
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:04,000
 And so I'm going to say a little part, and then you can make it your own words.

368
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:08,000
 So let me pray.

369
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:12,000
 Dear Jesus,

370
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:21,000
 I now turn away from all that I've done that is wrong.

371
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:26,000
 And now you can actually tell Jesus the things that you've done that were wrong and just ask Him for forgiveness on your own.

372
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:27,000
 Just tell Him right now.

373
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:29,000
 Maybe it's that hurtful word.

374
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:31,000
 Maybe it's some action that you've done.

375
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:42,000
 Just tell Him.

376
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:46,000
 Please forgive me.

377
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:55,000
 I now turn away from all that is wrong.

378
00:22:55,000 --> 00:23:12,000
 And thank you, Jesus, that you died for me on the cross to forgive my sins and to set me free.

379
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:22,000
 I now receive this gift of forgiveness and the gift of your Holy Spirit.

380
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:36,000
 Will you come into my life by your Holy Spirit and will be with me forever?

381
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:40,000
 Thank you, Lord Jesus.

382
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:46,000
 Amen.

383
00:23:46,000 --> 00:24:00,000
 So let's not just celebrate the mood of Christmas, the dazzling lights, the imported foods or the dinners or lunches or whatever you do, but miss Jesus in all of that.

384
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:03,000
 Let's celebrate the meaning of Christmas.

385
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:09,000
 You know, we receive the gift which is Him that gives us great joy.

386
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:11,000
 I love you all.

387
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:13,000
 Merry Christmas.

388
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:17,000
 Let's stand up and let's worship.

389
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:19,000
 Thank you, Pastor Tim.

390
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:21,000
 30 minutes ago we sang this song.

391
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:24,000
 I hope after this message we'll sing it differently.

